commText: CSK in their huddle as KL and QdK walk out. Deepak Chahar to take the new ball as usual and he has a slip in place
-- KL Rahul became the second wicketkeeper to effect three dismissals in an innings for LSG, after Quinton de Kock, who had done that against SRH in Hyderabad last year.
Dhoni batting in the 20th over in the IPL Runs: 772 Balls: 313 SR: 246.64 4s/6s: 53/65 I0$ 57 off 16, four fours, six sixes (SR: 356.25)
CSK innings progression Overs 1-6: 51/2 (RR: 8.5) Overs 7-16: 62/3 (RR: 6.2) Overs 17-20: 63/1 (RR: 15.75)
-- This was the second instance of Jadeja facing 40 or more balls in an IPL innings, after his 37 off 44 for RR vs PBKS in Cape Town back in 2009.
Jadeja vs spin in the IPL \n2015 to 2023: 336 off 350, Avg: 22.4, SR: 96, 4s/6s: 13/13, Dots: 143 \n2024: 32 off 20, no dismissal, SR: 160, 4s/6s: 3/1, Dots: 4

Cloth being run across the outfield to take off any bit of dew. CSK have two good spin options in Jadeja and Mo today. Deepak Chahar is back too. LSG need to bat really well to get this total. Their middle-order has been misfiring and today is a great chance to correct that. Can they counter Pathirana?

21:13 Local Time, 15:43 GMT, 21:13 IST: This football-loving youngster just comes and tees off however tough the conditions are. Wankhede wasn't a tough pitch to bat on, but today it wasn't exactly a belter and most of his teammates couldn't inject life but here he comes running down the stairs with a knee to be managed and uses his experience and street-smarts to strike at 300+. CSK now have a total to fight should dew not have a large say. LSG had a good powerplay with Mohsin and Yash getting Rachin and Rutu cheaply. Jinks Rahane played a very useful innings and CSK promoted Jadeja today to hold one end up and he did a great job. Dube fell cheaply. Moeen and Jaddu had to rebuild and Mo took a calculated risk against Bishnoi to get a hat-trick of sixes and when 160 looked tough, Dhoni made 176 possible.

Yash Thakur to Dhoni, FOUR, oh outstanding from Dhoni! You can't complain about that ball one bit. A perfectly executed wide yorker, just that Dhoni was too good to squeeze it out past backward point and third man was inside too. Yet another game where Dhoni's late surge lifts the CSK team

Yash Thakur to Dhoni, 2 runs, full and on the stumps, Dhoni whips it away to deep mid-wicket. Again good from Yash Thakur to not allows the master to get under the ball. Can he do it for one more ball?

Yash Thakur to Dhoni, FOUR, edgeddd away for four! You got to give credit to the bowler here. He actually bowled a pretty good off-side yorker but Dhoni with his muscular bat swing has got a thick edge that spun and beat short third man to the left

Yash Thakur to Dhoni, SIX, baaaang! Six number 65 in the 20th over! Absolute slot ball and Dhoni milked it properly. Round the wicket and in the arc, out of the park went MSD. This is trouble for LSG. If Yash Thakur keeps trying yorkers he could he taken for runs here
What will be the plan from Yash Thakur? The bigger boundary is the leg-side now but he can't offer anything in the slot and boundary size doesn't matter to this man
Yash Thakur to Jadeja, 1 run, low full toss, smacked to mid-off and Dhoni back on strike
Yash Thakur to Jadeja, 2 runs, full toss, Jadeja mistimes the drive to deep cover, Dhoni says two and he's back
Yash Thakur [3.0-0-26-1] is back into the attack
170 is easily on now.
Mohsin Khan to Dhoni, no run, oh beaten! Lovely slower delivery angling across, Dhoni slogged hard across the line and missed
Mohsin Khan to Dhoni, wide, this is surely a wide. Short and too high
Mohsin Khan to Jadeja, 1 run, short and into the wicket, Jadeja slaps it to deep point
KL asking the bowler to have clarity in his plans
Mohsin Khan to Jadeja, no run, short delivery rising high, Jaddu pulls and misses. Given wide, not exactly over his head and LSG get it changed with the review
LSG review for a wide call. Ball not completely over says third ump. Fair delivery!
Mohsin Khan to Dhoni, 1 run, slower delivery, Dhoni dabs to deep backward point

Mohsin Khan to Dhoni, SIX, oh ho ho! MS Dhoni walking across the stumps and trying to scoop. That's a rarity and if he's going to play such shots the bowler will be under even more pressure. Short of a length delivery on the stumps, Dhoni moves off-side and scoops it over KL and it flies off the bat off the outer half of the bat. Almost the top edge
Mohsin Khan to Dhoni, FOUR, in the airrr, Bishnoi can't get it with the dive at deep extra! Full and outside off stump, Dhoni reaches out and lofts it on the bounce for four

Mohsin Khan to Dhoni, wide, Dhoni reviews for a wide. Third ump says it's outside the line and it stays a wide. Seemed like a 50-50 call real time and the onfield ump gave the benefit of doubt to the bowler. Replays showed ball just outside the line and Dhoni was taking a middle stump guard
Mohsin Khan to Dhoni, wide, straightaway the plan is bowl wide of off and it's a wide. Understand the plan because it's a bigger boundary on the off-side at this end
One over of Moshin and the other Thakur maybe? If Dhoni bats till the end, CSK could get that 170 mark
Ravi Bishnoi to Dhoni, 1 run, low full toss outside off stump, Dhoni drives to long-off and keeps strike
MS Dhoni, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Crowd in full voices as MS Dhoni walks down the stairs and to the middle. Now pressure on LSG pacers with him at the crease for the last two overs

Ravi Bishnoi to Moeen Ali, out Caught by Ayush Badoni!! In the airrr and taken. Credit to Ravi Bishnoi for sticking to what his strengths were. Too bowl googlies to LHBs with a big leg-side boundary and he got the length spot on. Was really full and Mo couldn't properly get under the ball like he did earlier in the over and it's gone flat to deep mid-wicket. But he's made that impact with the bat. Moeen Ali c Ayush Badoni b Ravi Bishnoi 30(20) [6s-3]
Ravi Bishnoi to Moeen Ali, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Ravi Bishnoi to Moeen Ali, SIX, very predictable! With Mo targetting the leg-side, Bishnoi was going to bowl short and across him and Mo was just waiting for it off the back foot and smacks it off the back foot over long-off. Hat-trick of sixes now
Ravi Bishnoi to Moeen Ali, SIX, and again! This time goes behind square. It's full, it's slot, Mo goes down on one knee and nails that slog sweep that he plays well. CSK badly needed those maximums
Ravi Bishnoi to Moeen Ali, SIX, Mo nails the slog sweep. This time the line is closer to the stumps so Mo able to connect the ball really well and hits it over deep square leg for six
Bishnoi is going to bowl nothing but googlies to LHBs. This is a double-edged sword
Ravi Bishnoi to Moeen Ali, no run, oh full googly down leg, Mo slogs and misses, gets hit on the pad. Well down leg though
Ravi Bishnoi [3.0-0-25-0] is back into the attack
Mohsin Khan to Moeen Ali, 1 run, short delivery, Mo mistimes the pull to fine leg
Mohsin Khan to Jadeja, 1 run, into the wicket, Jadeja drags it through backward square leg
Mohsin Khan to Jadeja, no run, shortish delivery, Jadeja swings and misses

Mohsin Khan to Jadeja, SIX, oh dropped and six! That should have been taken. Meanwhile Ravi Jadeja brings out his trademark sword celebration for his fifty. He does it in Tests and ODIs but this is the first time in a long. long time that we are seeing him do this in the IPL because he doesn't face that many balls. Full delivery cramping Jadeja for room, Jadeja lofts down the ground. Hooda was at long-on, was overhead but he spills the catch as he was too close to the rope
Mohsin Khan to Moeen Ali, 1 run, Mo has been picking out fielders. Was a short slower delivery, pulls and gets only one
Mohsin Khan to Jadeja, 1 run, again Jadeja moves very early to the off-side with the intention of scooping on the on-side, but Mohsin smartly fires the slower delivery wide of off stump and dabs
Mohsin Khan [2.0-0-12-1] is back into the attack

Over Summary (12-16): -- Dube has a rare off day as he falls for 3 to Stoinis -- Rizvi comes in as Impact sub -- Rizvi fails to make any impact as he is stumped off Krunal for 1 -- Stoinis bowls a tight over -- Jadeja and Ali conjure up some runs
Yash Thakur to Moeen Ali, no run, oh pace off and he tried to smack it through cover, toe-ended the drive straight to hand. Missed out there
Yash Thakur to Moeen Ali, 2 runs, carved away past backward point as Yash Thakur tries to fire this wide of off stump, two added
Yash Thakur to Jadeja, 1 run, shuffles in the crease but the bowler keeps his calm and nails a very good off-side yorker, dug out to cover

Yash Thakur to Jadeja, FOUR, this is the batter playing on the bowler's mind. Jaddu again shaping up for a sweep/scoop over short fine leg. Seeing that Yash Thakur tries to fire this way outside off stump but he fell in the trap there because third man was in too and Jaddu easily guided it for four
Yash Thakur to Jadeja, no run, Jadeja knees down for the sweep spotting backward square leg and fine leg in but he mistimes this wide low full toss to the former
Yash Thakur to Moeen Ali, 1 run, so Yash gets his third now. Starts off with a slower delivery outside off stump, Mo drives to long-off
Yash Thakur [2.0-0-18-1] is back into the attack

Timeout. LSG slipping in extra overs from their 6th bowler quota has ensured they don't need to bowl out one of their frontliners. Bishnoi likely to bowl one more. Mohsin two more and the remaining two could be rotated according to match scenario. They will hope dew sets in now to ease the pitch for their batting innings
Ravi Bishnoi to Moeen Ali, 1 run, dab and run single to backward point
Ravi Bishnoi to Jadeja, 1 run, googly, Jadeja looks to loft, bit of a mishit and it goes to long-off
Ravi Bishnoi to Moeen Ali, 1 run, goes back and nicely guides this shortish delivery to deep cover
Ravi Bishnoi to Jadeja, 1 run, easy nudge to mid-wicket now off the front foot
Ravi Bishnoi to Jadeja, 2 runs, worked away to mid-wicket and they get back for two
Ravi Bishnoi to Moeen Ali, 1 run, Mo dabs this googly to backward point
Ravi Bishnoi [2.0-0-18-0] is back into the attack

Six overs to go. Doesn't seem to be a flat pitch but 160 is a minimum that's needed and Dhoni, as told by Mike Hussey earlier, because of his knee issue not in a position to bat more than the 3-4 overs
Stoinis to Jadeja, 2 runs, over the wicket for this short slower delivery, Jadeja pulls behind square and gets back for two
Stoinis to Moeen Ali, 1 run, slower delivery, Mo taps it to point
Stoinis to Moeen Ali, no run, fairly fine cover drive, but picks out the fielder in the ring
Stoinis to Jadeja, 1 run, short and slow outside off stump, Jaddu wanted a pull off the back foot, toe-ended to the vacant mid-on region
Stoinis to Moeen Ali, 1 run, short of length delivery outside off stump, Mo punches it to deep backward point
LSG doing well to buy some cheap overs
Stoinis to Moeen Ali, no run, round the wicket. Length delivery pushed towards cover
Krunal Pandya to Moeen Ali, 1 run, 100.5kph, pad-lined, flicked to deep backward square leg. Another good over from Krunal!
Krunal Pandya to Jadeja, 1 run, 95.1kph, gives a bit of flight on this occasion does Krunal Pandya. Jadeja leans forward to drive it to long-off
Krunal Pandya to Moeen Ali, 1 run, away-dart, dabbed towards short third man for a single
Krunal Pandya to Moeen Ali, no run, quick on middle, turned to midwicket
Moeen Ali, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Krunal Pandya to Sameer Rizvi, out Stumped!! CSK have now lost half their side. 102.9kph, Sameer Rizvi waltzes down the track premeditatively. Has a wild swing at it in an attempt to send it out of the stadium. Krunal Pandya sees that and pulls his length back. The batsman fails to make contact and Rahul does the rest. The impact sub never looked comfortable in his brief stay at the crease. Sameer Rizvi st Rahul b Krunal Pandya 1(5)
Krunal Pandya to Sameer Rizvi, THATS OUT!! Stumped!!
Ajinkya Rahane vs Krunal Pandya in T20s Runs: 52 Balls: 48 Dismissals: 4 Avg: 13 SR: 108.33
Krunal Pandya to Jadeja, 1 run, 97.8kph, middle-stump line, Jadeja stays back to flick it to midwicket
Krunal Pandya [2.0-0-12-1] is back into the attack
Stoinis to Jadeja, 1 run, 128.9kph, round the wicket, shortish ball and that's been jabbed to deep midwicket
Stoinis to Sameer Rizvi, 1 run, 136kph, fullish delivery angled in on leg, clipped away to deep square leg to get off the mark
Stoinis to Sameer Rizvi, no run, 126kph, back of a length, Rizvi can only push it to midwicket
Stoinis to Sameer Rizvi, no run, wow! In-seamer from a short of length, Rizvi looks to flick it away and gets beaten on the inside edge. Over the sticks and Rahul dives to his right to stop it
Stoinis to Sameer Rizvi, no run, back of a length on off, Sameer Rizvi hops and nudges it into the on-side
Sameer Rizvi, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Rizvi comes in as the Impact Player! He replaces Rahane...

Stoinis to Shivam Dube, out Caught by Rahul!! Stoinis strikes first ball and it's the big wicket! 125.4kph, shortish ball and Shivam Dube shapes to pull it powerfully over midwicket. Slices it in the air and Rahul calls for it. Runs in towards the short point region and takes it calmly. The in-form Dube departs cheaply. Shivam Dube c Rahul b Stoinis 3(8)
Stoinis to Shivam Dube, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Marcus Stoinis, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Stoinis hasn't bowled much this seaon but KL brings him on against these two left-handers
Over Summary (7-11): -- Bishnoi concedes 11 in his first over -- Krunal gets rid of Rahane for 36 -- Dube and Jadeja reconstruct the innings a little
Yash Thakur to Shivam Dube, 1 run, 126.3kph, slower ball on a short length, Dube pulls it through midwicket with his front leg off the ground. Tidy over from Thakur
Yash Thakur to Shivam Dube, no run, 126.1kph, head-high bouncer, Dube is early into his pull and misses. The ball goes over the blade, Rahul fails to gather it cleanly but it isn't costly
Over the wicket to Shivam Dube and round the wicket to Jadeja

Yash Thakur to Jadeja, leg byes, 1 run, 136.1kph, Jadeja misses the flick against this full delivery and the ball rolls to square leg off the pad. Optimistic shout for lbw but that's clearly missing leg
Yash Thakur to Shivam Dube, 1 run, 123.2kph, off-speed short delivery, pulled along the ground to deep backward square leg
Yash Thakur to Jadeja, 1 run, 122.5kph, pace off, back of a length, turned towards backward square leg
Yash Thakur to Jadeja, 2 runs, 135kph, round the wicket, straying onto the pads, Jadeja misses the flick and the ball goes between the keeper and short fine leg off the pad. Given as runs though
Yash Thakur [1.0-0-13-1] is back into the attack
Ravi Bishnoi to Shivam Dube, no run, 97.5kph, lovely delivery! Length ball, lands on off and spins away to beat the outside edge of Shivam Dube who shapes to push-drive
A slip in place for Shivam Dube as well
Ravi Bishnoi to Jadeja, 1 run, 102.8kph, quicker one on the stumps, nudged into the midwicket pocket for a single

Ravi Bishnoi to Jadeja, FOUR, 90.1kph, cracking sweep shot! Gets low, fetches this from well outside off and brooms it fiercely through the vacant midwicket region. Bishnoi has a wry smile on his face
Ravi Bishnoi to Jadeja, no run, 91.1kph, steers this googly with the spin to short third man
Ravi Bishnoi to Jadeja, 2 runs, 93.1kph, wristed through wide mid-on and the batters decide to come back for the second. Good running
Ravi Bishnoi to Jadeja, no run, 99.6kph, wrong 'un from a short of length, stabbed to the right of cover and Stoinis makes a superb stop
Rahul persists with Bishnoi. No there's a slip in place
Krunal Pandya to Jadeja, 1 run, leg-lined, worked through midwicket and Jadeja calls for two but sends his partner back as Bishnoi is swift to get to the ball and release it
Krunal Pandya to Jadeja, FOUR, 94.4kph, non-turner down leg and Jadeja sweeps it fine of short fine leg. Tickled it very fine
Krunal Pandya to Shivam Dube, 1 run, 98.5kph, rocks back to pull hard and inside-halves to deep midwicket for a single
Krunal Pandya to Shivam Dube, no run, 100.8kph, defensively pushed to the right of the bowler

Krunal Pandya to Shivam Dube, no run, 99.2kph, round the wicket, short of length, Dube looks to work it into the leg-side and gets beaten on the inside edge. The ball dies down on the leg-side off his thigh pad
Shivam Dube, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Strategic timeout! LSG will be the happier side having removed CSK's top three. Jadeja has got a promotion today and once again the onus will be on Dube to provide the impetus in the middle overs, especially against the spinners. Do LSG have a plan against the big-hitter? Let's find out....

Krunal Pandya to Rahane, out Bowled!! Timber! 94.6kph, darted in on a length, Rahane looks to heave it across the line and misses it altogether. Beats the inside edge and crashes into the leg-stump. Rahane b Krunal Pandya 36(24) [4s-5 6s-1]
Krunal Pandya to Rahane, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!

Ravi Bishnoi to Jadeja, FOUR, Rahul shakes his head! There was a slip for Jadeja earlier in this over, not on this occasion. Would have gone straight to him had there been one., 92.8kph, googly around off, Jadeja gets forward and pushes with hard hands. Thick outside edge and the ball dribbles away fine of short third man. 11 runs off the over despite Bishnoi bowling really well
Ravi Bishnoi to Rahane, 1 run, 103.8kph, googly, Rahane backs away but he can't free his arms, knocks it to long-on for a single
Ravi Bishnoi to Rahane, FOUR, 92.1kph, googly, Rahane gets down on one leg to sweep and toe-ends it through midwicket. The ball has the legs to go to the fence
Ravi Bishnoi to Rahane, no run, 100.2kph, Rahane backs away, Bishnoi sees that and bowls a quick one from a short of length. Rahane pulls it to short fine leg off the inner edge
Ravi Bishnoi to Jadeja, 1 run, 100.3kph, quicker one marginally outside off, cut to deep point off the back foot
A slip in place now
Ravi Bishnoi to Rahane, 1 run, starts with a googly and that's been turned to midwicket
Ravi Bishnoi, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Spin from both ends!
Krunal Pandya to Rahane, 1 run, 97.7kph, flat and quick on the stumps, Rahane stays in his crease to work it through midwicket
Krunal Pandya to Rahane, 2 runs, 97.4kph, wristed to the right of long-on for a couple of runs
Krunal Pandya to Jadeja, 1 run, 97.8kph, stays back to flick and the ball rolls to backward square leg off the thigh pad. He got an inside edge though
Krunal Pandya to Rahane, 1 run, 96kph, in-dart on middle and leg, Rahane helps it on its way to short fine leg. A slight fumble from the fielder
Krunal Pandya to Jadeja, 1 run, 99.4kph, another one darted in on leg and middle, turned through square leg
Krunal Pandya to Jadeja, no run, 100.1kph, round the wicket, quick on the sticks, clipped to midwicket
Krunal Pandya, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack

Over Summary (1-6): -- Rahane opens, again, gets off the mark with a four -- Ravindra is bowled for a golden duck by Mohsin Khan -- Rahane and Ruturaj collect 13 off the second over of Henry -- Yash Thakur removes the CSK skipper for 17 -- Jadeja promoted to number 4 in the batting order -- Rahane off to a flier

This is just the 15th time that Ravindra Jadeja is batting in top four in T20 cricket (11th time at No.4, four times at No.3) in 317 T20 matches (227 innings). The last instance of him batting at No.4 in the format came against Pakistan in Dubai during the Asia Cup 2022.
Matt Henry to Jadeja, 1 run, 129.2kph, another slower ball, driven towards mid-off for a sharp single
Matt Henry to Rahane, 1 run, 115.5kph, pace off, off-cutter, leg-lined, glanced to deep midwicket
Matt Henry to Jadeja, 1 run, 121.4kph, full delivery angled in, clipped to the right of midwicket who makes a sliding stop
Matt Henry to Rahane, 1 run, slower delivery and that's been pushed towards mid-on for a single
Matt Henry to Jadeja, 1 run, 130.2kph, Henry pulls his length back and that's been turned to square leg
Matt Henry to Jadeja, FOUR, 134.9kph, pitched up ball from round the wicket, Jadeja backs away and plays a bold shot. Goes hard on the drive and lifts it over the jumping mid-off fielder
Matt Henry [2.0-0-17-0] is back into the attack

Yash Thakur to Rahane, FOUR, 132.6kph, loopy full delivery outside off and Rahane comes on the front foot to play an aerial drive over extra cover. Neatly timed and the man in the deep has no chance to stop that. End of an eventful over!

Yash Thakur to Rahane, FOUR, 129.2kph, short of a good length ball just outside off, Rahane opens his bat-face late. The ball trims the outside edge and goes fine of short third man before dribbling away to the fence
Yash Thakur to Jadeja, 1 run, 136.9kph, short of length, Jadeja backs away to cut it to deep backward point
Yash Thakur to Jadeja, no run, 133.9kph, length ball outside off from round the wicket, might have seamed away a touch, Jadeja sticks his bat out and is beaten on the outside edge
Ravindra Jadeja, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Yash Thakur to Gaikwad, out Caught by Rahul!! FOUR and OUT! Yash Thakur strikes second ball. 137.7kph, length ball outside off, Gaikwad presses forward to drive and only manages to get an outside edge as the ball seams away a touch. Not much bounce on this occasion and Rahul dives low to his right to gobble it up. Gaikwad c Rahul b Yash Thakur 17(13) [4s-1]
Yash Thakur to Gaikwad, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Yash Thakur to Gaikwad, FOUR, 138.9kph, Yash Thakur greeted with a boundary. Length ball outside off, Gaikwad opens the bat-face and expertly guides it between short third man and backward point. Uses the bowler's pace and width to his advantage
Yash Thakur, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
First bowling change. LSG continue to operate with pace. No slips...

Mohsin Khan to Rahane, FOUR, edged and four! 135.6kph, short of length ball, Rahane walks across towards off to muscle it over mid-on/midwicket, gets a fat edge that flies over short third man. A streaky boundary to end the over!
Mohsin Khan to Rahane, no run, 119.7kph, off-speed shortish ball, Rahane taps it towards short third man
Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, 1 run, 140.9kph, fuller than a length outside off, Gaikwad gets forward to drive and miscues it to mid-off
Mohsin Khan to Rahane, 1 run, 139.1kph, square-driven to deep point
Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, 1 run, 120.8kph, pace off, fuller and wider, Gaikwad reaches out to drive and Stoinis makes a diving stop to his left at extra cover
Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, 2 runs, 136.2kph, short of length ball around off, Gaikwad hangs back to punch it through point for a couple of runs

Matt Henry to Rahane, SIX, 133.7kph, harmless short ball around the waist, sits up nicely for Rahane who stands tall and pulls it handsomely over deep midwicket. Authoritative hit. 13 runs off the over!
Matt Henry to Gaikwad, 1 run, 137.3kph, back of a length, Gaikwad steers it behind square on the off-side
Matt Henry to Gaikwad, 2 runs, 133.1kph, in-slanter on middle and leg, Gaikwad stays leg-side and hurriedly opens his bat-face to guide it past short third man
Rachin Ravindra in IPL 2024: \nFirst two innings: 83(35), SR: 237.14 \nNext five innings: 50(46), Avg: 10, SR: 108.7
Matt Henry to Gaikwad, 2 runs, 132.6kph, full again, the line is outside off and Gaikwad eases the drive through the covers. QdK has to run to his right in the deep to cut it off
Matt Henry to Gaikwad, no run, 136.3kph, pitched up, a big stride forward from Gaikwad and he drives it straight to extra cover
Matt Henry to Gaikwad, 2 runs, 134.3kph, pitched up outside off, no movement, Gaikwad gets forward and drives with an opened bat-face. Deep point runs across and makes a sliding stop to his left
Mohsin Khan to Rahane, no run, 139.2kph, fuller length outside off, Rahane drives with not much feet movement and inside-edges it back towards the bowler
Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, 1 run, 138.6kph, short of length ball around off, a hopping Gaikwad guides it to the right of short third man who makes a diving stop
Ruturaj Gaikwad has been dismissed thrice by left-arm pacers in this IPL!
Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, no run, 135.8kph, Mohsin pulls his length back and that's been punched to point
Mohsin Khan to Rahane, 1 run, 130.1kph, looked like the slower ball from Mohsin Khan, Rahane plays with soft hands and drops it in front of point for a single
Mohsin Khan to Gaikwad, 1 run, 137.5kph, hint of inward shape, Gaikwad stays back, taps it into the off-side and gets off the mark with a quick single
Ruturaj Gaikwad, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Mohsin Khan to Ravindra, out Bowled!! Cleaned up! Ravindra departs for a golden duck. 134.3kph, full and angling in, nips in a bit and Ravindra doesn't account for the movement as he shapes to drive. Plays outside the line, the ball beats the inside edge and crashes into the stumps. Perfect start for Mohsin Khan! Ravindra b Mohsin Khan 0(1)
Mohsin Khan to Ravindra, THATS OUT!! Bowled!!
Mohsin Khan, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Two fielders outside the circle - deep point and deep square leg
Matt Henry to Rahane, no run, 137.2kph, short of a good length outside off, Rahane opens his bat-face and plays late to steer it to backward point
Matt Henry to Rahane, no run, 132.1kph, full ball, pushed to the left of the bowler
A wide slip in position
Matt Henry to Rahane, no run, 134kph, full again, Rahane's bat turns a bit as he gets half-forward to drive. Miscues towards mid-on
Matt Henry to Rahane, no run, 134.5kph, full delivery angled in on the sticks, driven to mid-on

Matt Henry to Rahane, FOUR, Rahane gets off the mark with a boundary! 133.4kph, width on offer and the batter pounces. Waits on the back foot and plays a cracking shot sending it through point. No movement for Matt Henry on that occasion
Matt Henry to Rahane, no run, 130.5kph, pitched up ball, bit of shape away from the right-hander, watchfully push-driven to mid-off
Rahane and Ravindra are at the crease. Rahane is on strike. Matt Henry will open the attack
